## 1ï¸âƒ£ units_audit.py
	â€¢	ğŸ“ What it does: Checks for unit consistency in equations and text (e.g., mixing SI with CGS units, or ambiguous custom units).
	â€¢	âœ… Flags:
	â€¢	--check-consistency to verify all units are in a single system (SI, CGS, etc.)
	â€¢	--flag-custom for author-defined units like â€œarb. units.â€
	â€¢	ğŸ§  Few-shot would teach it that â€œeVâ€ is valid, but â€œMeV/c^2â€ in a length equation isnâ€™t.


## ğŸ“‘ Citation Audit

Run a check to verify that all citations in your LaTeX file are defined in the bibliography and not fabricated.

ğŸ§¹ Dry Run:
```bash
